Microtuboplasty as an outpatient procedure.
 Fifteen cases of microtuboplasty were done as outpatient procedures at low cost and with increased patient convenience.
 Advances in outpatient surgery at free-standing surgery centers have allowed many new patient care innovations, and microsurgery should now be considered an outpatient procedure for gynecologic patients.
 Outpatient microtuboplastic surgery is not only feasible but perhaps preferable to that done as an inpatient procedure.
